reviews.text: What a fun place to go with a family that is really hungry and ready for some entertainment. This dining experience was entertaining from the start. Immediately as you get to the restaurant outside you have beautiful Japanese garden with some gorgeous prize-winning goldfishes. They kids had so much fun looking at them swimming and everything.  After all of that excitement we were able to be seated at a Japanese Hibachi Table with another family and kids so my children had a lot of fun interacting with everyone else around the table. As the chef came in he quickly started his show and it was fun interactive and very energetic. There was so much food!!!! Your portions are very large so make sure you come hungry. the typical Hibachi chicken dinner included rice vegetables and before that you get to have soup and salad. The only reason I took a star of was that the food was not as flavorful or authentic as I am used to but for being Japanese attraction chain spot it was sort of expected to be a little Bland however it was perfect for kiddos taste buds.

The food is surprisingly better than one might think. The salad that comes out with the soup prior to the meal is delicious I really like the dressing here. I did not care for the sushi as it did not seem as fresh as some places. The steak and chicken combo I ordered was well-cooked and affordable.

We arrived around 5:30, no one else in the dining area except for a group that was finishing up. We waited 15-20min before getting our drinks. A party of 16 arrived after we got our drinks. We had already ordered when another group joined our table. We still had not received our salads or soup an HOUR after being seated, but the party’s food was being cooked and served. Poor management. We were told that the party arrived before us, when they actually MOVED us from the table the party was sitting at to serve us quicker. The manager that I spoke with said “they knew what they wanted to eat, they had a list” I DON’T CARE if they had a list, we had ordered our food BEFORE the party placed their order. Waiting an hour and not receiving soups and salads is unacceptable in my book.

This place has always been pretty good. However the service has really gone down hill. No refills for the entire meal. Wrong food served. Appetizers brought after meal. Very small portions. Time to search for new place to eat.

Yes yes!! Best sushi presentation in Tennessee. Chef Boy knows how to make a birthday special. I told him to surprise me and yes I was surprised with a great sushi dinner.. will always be my go to place for sushi!!
Quiet place, very friendly staff and a broad enough menu to keep everyone guessing what they want. Lunch specials are around $10 with most entrees around $14. Great place for a quick bite.

Everyone here was so extremly nice to me and they all were stop helpful! (I've never eaten Thai before) The food was great, the drink was great & the service was just awesome! I wish all places were as friendly as they were here!

Came in today. Waited 45 mins thinking the food is almost ready. When I go and ask the worker about the wait time for food, she says it will take another 10 mins. Canceled the order and left with no food. Who takes 50+ mins to cook during lunch hour. Plus it was only one person serving all the customers and it took some time before she came to take our order. If you know it's going to be busy, have more people to help during peak hours. This is unacceptable. I would not give a star but that's the only option available. I would not recommend this place.

You couldn't ask for a better Panda the green beans and chicken was better than I've had anywhere it was super unlike the one that's over by the Vallarta store on Clinton and Weber this one here gets an A+ and that one over there gets an F don't bother to go there cuz their food is terrible. Also the help over here on Shaw is much more friendly and it's an all-around better experience
Place is decorated really nice for the holidays and food/service is good. Karaoke in the summer....

Amazing dinner last night 5 floors above our room! The view is gorgeous 😍😍 The staff is amazing and friendly. Boy oh boy it was the BEST food I have EVER had at a restaurant. The pork chop literally melted in my mouth and the brussel sprout leaves that came with was to die for! Highly highly recommend this place for special occasions!!!

Very fancy food. You definitely get what you pay for. I would recommend going when the sun is up or you will end up looking into the dark void that is Alaskan nights. Servers are on top of their game.

The service was wonderful, Ryan. The wine was very good. Love the setting and the scenery. The salmon was a too fresh. It was raw in the middle. Disappointed in the salmon. The squash soup was good. Very expensive.
Unbelievable experience, unlike any other! Incredible views and food. Pocketbook will be lighter after going here (we had four people in our group) but one of the best meals possible in Alaska!!!

I visit every month with my friends from the now defunct Rotary Club of Tring. My personal experience is therefore only relevant to Wednesday lunch times. The service on Wednesdays is very good, with two very friendly and helpful waitresses. The food is good value and would never claim to be Cordon Bleu. It is a good example of a pub serving traditional British food. Inexpensive and simple.
